## The Scholar's Burden

I sought to **acquire** all wisdom's light,  
A burning hunger, fierce and unconfined;  
Through dusty tomes I strained with all my might,  
To sate the endless craving of the mind.  

Each fragile page held secrets I desired,  
Complexities that set my thoughts ablaze;  
Yet deeper paths left confidence untired,  
A labyrinth obscured in shadowed haze.  

The **tearing** weight of volumes, vast and old,  
Began the slow, **fearful** erosion deep;  
