    *   "**tearing**" appears in line 9.
    *   "**fearful**" appears in line 11.
3.  **Structure & Theme:** A traditional Shakespearean sonnet structure (3 quatrains + couplet). The theme explores the arduous pursuit of knowledge ("acquire"), the physical and mental strain ("tearing" weight, "wearing" thin), and the anxiety and doubt that accompany deep learning ("fearful erosion"). The couplet offers a resolution: true understanding requires inner strength beyond mere book-learning.
